name: Preeti Udupi Restaurant

reviews.review_text: The food was great. My husband came here after 20 years! He was remembering his childhood times and the food he used to eat here. It’s great the place is still in business. The food was really good. The idlis and the coconut chutney were the bomb. The idli has so unique fermented rice flavor and so fluffy spongy and the chutney is fresh grated coconut and spices, not sweet at all which is the best part. Full of flavor! The mix veg khorma was also great. And the special tea was super fresh and flavorful. Loved it. Puri was fluffy and delicious! The cheese masala dosa was amazing with lots of amul cheese and the potato masala inside was perfect blend of spices and deliciousness. Everything costed $2.77!

The food tasted good. They can maintain the atmosphere even more well. We took Puri, idli, upittu,sira, vada, aloo bonda and dahi vada all tasted awesome. I recommend this hotel if you are looking for veg in Madgon.

I've recently had a very bad experience, i was hungry placing an order and the person taking the order simply just ignored my order and walked off deaf ear. I would recommend people to be very persistent with what you need. Because the waiters here seem exhausted and frustrated to simply wait and listen to take down your order. I'm very much disappointed with the service.

description:
**Restaurant Review: Preeti Udupi Restaurant**

Tucked away in the lively area of Aquem, Preeti Udupi Restaurant offers a nostalgic yet vibrant dining experience with an overall rating of 3.6 stars from a robust feedback pool of 885 reviewers. With a focus on vegetarian cuisine, this eatery is particularly noted for its affordability, with prices highlighted in numerous reviews and an emphasis on beloved dishes like **pav bhaji**, **puri bhaji**, and various snacks, making it a popular spot for both families and food enthusiasts.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon entering Preeti Udupi, guests immediately notice a simple yet welcoming atmosphere. The décor blends traditional elements with a casual dining vibe—an inviting environment where the chatter of happy diners mingles with the aroma of spices wafting from the kitchen. The lighting maintains a warm glow, perfect for casual dining, although some reviewers have expressed that the overall ambiance could use a touch more attention. The casual seating arrangement complements the bustling spirit of the locality, making it a cheerful destination for a satisfying meal.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Preeti Udupi showcases a delightful array of vegetarian dishes characterized by their rich flavors and authentic preparation. Signature dishes like fluffy **idlis** paired with a vibrant **coconut chutney**, **cheese masala dosa** — bursting with melting Amul cheese and perfectly spiced potato filling — and the ever-popular **puri bhaji** have received high praise from many customers. One review notably describes the idli as possessing a "unique fermented rice flavor" and praises the freshness of the chutney, which eschews sweetness for a more grounded spice palette. Meanwhile, the special tea served is described as "super fresh and flavorful,” a fitting companion to a richly varied meal that can be enjoyed without breaking the bank. Customers appreciate that many of these scrumptious plates come at an astonishingly low price, with some meals costing under $3.

**Customer Experience & Service**

While the culinary offerings tend to win hearts, customer service experiences appear to vary widely. Several patrons commend the staff for their efficiency and friendliness, making their dining experiences more enjoyable. However, a contrasting sentiment comes from a dissatisfied diner who faced lackluster attention from the service team during a busy period, highlighting a need for improvement in communication and attentiveness. Reviewers encourage future customers to be persistent when placing orders, as service can occasionally feel overwhelmed, detracting from an otherwise enjoyable visit.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Despite the service hiccups, Preeti Udupi maintains a loyal customer base with many expressing fond memories tied to the establishment. The reviews are filled with sentiments of reminiscence, with at least one patron returning after two decades, showcasing the restaurant’s deep roots in the community. Known among locals for exceptional vegetarian offerings, the restaurant frequently appears in conversations around the best spots for snacks in Madgaon, particularly for its authentic Indian street food vibe.

**Visual Appeal**

The restaurant's charm is accentuated by the visual journey captured in customer-uploaded images. Photos display the colorful and appealing presentation of the food, from the golden crust of **puri** floating atop fragrant curries to the hearty, inviting stacks of **idlis** served with fresh chutney. The images also effectively portray the restaurant’s vibrant, bustling essence, inviting prospective diners to bask in the joy of a well-spent meal.

In summary, Preeti Udupi Restaurant promises a delightful dive into authentic vegetarian cuisine at wallet-friendly prices, with the caveat of fluctuating service performance. Whether seeking a casual snack or a fulfilling meal, this restaurant stands as a cherished destination in Aquem, eager to stir nostalgia and tantalize taste buds alike.
